<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="746" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d746">
                            <head>No. 743.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bliss</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-24"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 24,
                                        1873</date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The President desires the examination mentioned in my letter of
                                yesterday to be attended on the part of the Government, and the
                                facts of the case to be fairly and fully ascertained. He wishes no
                                delay interposed; but if you think it necessary for the full
                                ascertainment of the facts, you will continue or adjourn the
                                examination.</p>
                            <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary of
                                        State.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>